# Week 6 â€“ Day 4: Object-Oriented Programming (OOPS) in C++

## ðŸ“Œ Overview
Object-Oriented Programming (OOPS) is a programming paradigm based on the concept of "objects" that contain data and methods.  
C++ supports OOPS to make programs more modular, reusable, and easier to maintain.

---

## ðŸ§  Key OOPS Concepts Covered

1. Class & Object  
2. Constructors  
3. Encapsulation  
4. Inheritance  
5. Polymorphism  
6. Abstraction  

